This paper discusses the measurement of fluency in human-robot collaboration, which is a topic that falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a model for measuring fluency using temporal constraint networks, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The focus on human-robot interaction and collaboration suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of temporal constraint networks and the proposed metrics for measuring fluency suggest that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
